                  <birth when="1861"/>
                  
                  
                  
               <floruit notBefore="1881" notAfter="1930">He was one of  
                  Ethiopia's most prominent artists during the reign of 
                  
                  <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Mǝnilǝk</persName>. 
                  He was one of the first Ethiopians to go abroad to study painting, 
                  in <placeName ref="wd:Q142"/>. His painting include illustration for a copy of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2384Taamme"/>. ʾElyās Ḫāylu also decorated many churches and he was one of the 
                  first Ethiopian artists to depict  <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Mǝnilǝk</persName> 's victory at the battle of 
                  <placeName ref="LOC1263Adwa"/>. 
                  </floruit>
                  <death notAfter="1930"/>
                  
                  
